              I personally think it may be an overreaction.  OK, I did not exploit the bug so I can not comment on the crazy 425 level monsters.  I did fight level 90 and 100 monsters so I can comment on that.  I fought the level 90's a bit mainly because I got so much more XP for my mana, despite the fact they were very dangerous (they are/were those spiders that shoot electricity like a machine gun).  I was able to three hit them with boulders with a Power Focus (whereas they hit me about 10 times) while the Battlesnakes took about 7 hits.  The battlesnakes represented no danger at all, with appropriate spells I could fight three at once and suffer virtually no damage.  I want to clarify that I had earth spells only, was a pure Cleric, and if I had water spells that whole situation would have been different.  The point of all this is that I chose a far more dangerous monster, worth less experience per monster, because of my ability to damage it.  I levelled faster based only on that criteria.  If they increased the magical resistances of creatures I am of the opinion that it alone would be sufficient be redress the issues regarding mages having an easier time in the Collosseum, provided they were fighting legitimate monsters (which their other corrections would seemingly fix).  Making them shoot faster would just make it boring, people would be forced to face creatures that could not hurt them (like the snakes, 20 x 0 is no greater than 15 x 0) and it would be even more boring.  <br><br>My opinion is the Collosseum is a bad idea.  It is incredibly boring and ugly and could be the result of them running out of money and not having the time to do something like Mad's House or the Lost Forest.  That is pure speculation.  It would be relatively trivial to write something that simple compared to the Arakas and RD counterparts.  The Collosseum adds nothing to the game, it is nothing new or interesting.  The complete predictability makes it as interesting as watching grass grow (except grass has a variable rate of growth, if only it were possible to detect it with the human eye.  Sigh).  You know the monster (after the first time), you know where he will be, you know he will not drop anything, and you know how many of them there will be.  Just very boring, in my opinion anyway.  Trash the stupid thing and stop the warriors from their incessant complaining.  For the Seraph's who claim they deserve and advantage, they already have a big one they may not understand.  You can fight MOBS of monsters now, for the simple reason that the wings heal like mad when you have lots of guys on you.  It changes the dynamics of levelling a bit, but if you use it properly you can level much faster than you would be capable of without the wings.  If you fight one on one against more a powerful monster, you forfeit much of the benefit.  For warriors who complain so much, just be a Paladin like anyone with a brain would be (which means increasing AC so you can handle a mob too) and get EQ and an Emerald Power Focus.  It works like a charm and you can maximize your Seraph benefit.  Even after getting boulders EQ in a mob was a better choice for levelling, for me.  And like I said, the wings heal like mad.<br><br><br>
            <br><br>
          </td>
        </tr>
      
